01:06:32,101 --> 01:06:35,730
A house, kids, certain schools,
a home in Connecticut.

943
01:06:35,938 --> 01:06:38,236
lt`s all very preconceived.

944
01:06:38,441 --> 01:06:41,740
Yeah, but l--
l thought you needed that.

945
01:06:41,944 --> 01:06:44,310
You said your life was chaos.

946
01:06:44,514 --> 01:06:47,745
But there`s got to be
some give and take.

947
01:06:47,950 --> 01:06:51,386
l don`t know what the hell
l`m talking about.

948
01:06:52,121 --> 01:06:54,453
-Are you angry with me?
-No.

949
01:06:54,657 --> 01:06:58,218
Do you feel--? Are you disenchanted
with our marriage?

950
01:06:58,428 --> 01:06:59,486
l didn`t say that.

951
01:06:59,696 --> 01:07:01,254
ls there someone else?

952
01:07:01,464 --> 01:07:04,160
What is this? The Gestapo? No.

953
01:07:04,867 --> 01:07:06,664
What are you not telling me?

954
01:07:06,869 --> 01:07:07,995
What kind of--?

955
01:07:08,204 --> 01:07:10,798
Supposing l said l am disenchanted.

956
01:07:11,007 --> 01:07:13,669
-l am in love with someone else.
-Are you?

957
01:07:13,910 --> 01:07:15,104
No.

958
01:07:15,311 --> 01:07:20,214
You keep asking these questions.
lt`s like you want me to say yes.

959
01:07:20,416 --> 01:07:24,147
What are you saying?
Of course not. l`d be destroyed.

960
01:07:24,354 --> 01:07:27,221
For chrissake,
stop torturing her.

961
01:07:27,423 --> 01:07:30,153
Say you want out
and get it over with.

962
01:07:30,360 --> 01:07:31,827
You love her sister.

963
01:07:32,028 --> 01:07:34,155
You didn`t do it on purpose.

964
01:07:34,364 --> 01:07:37,265
Be honest. It`s always the best way.

965
01:07:37,467 --> 01:07:39,935
Can l help you?

966
01:07:40,169 --> 01:07:43,900
lf you`re suffering over something,
share it with me.

967
01:07:46,409 --> 01:07:48,502
You know how much l love you.

968
01:07:50,680 --> 01:07:54,309
l should have my head examined.
l don`t deserve you.

969
01:08:01,724 --> 01:08:06,252
l wanna look good, but l don`t
want to be overdressed.

970
01:08:06,462 --> 01:08:11,195
-How about this?
-l think it`s a pretty color on you.

971
01:08:11,401 --> 01:08:14,666
Ever think you`d see me
going to the opera?

972
01:08:14,871 --> 01:08:16,998
lt`s great. l want to meet him.

973
01:08:17,206 --> 01:08:21,540
He`s married. And
his wife`s schizophrenic.

974
01:08:21,744 --> 01:08:24,542
Sometimes she just breaks down.

975
01:08:24,747 --> 01:08:27,739
When his daughter
goes to college next year...

976
01:08:27,950 --> 01:08:29,747
...he`ll split permanently.

977
01:08:29,952 --> 01:08:33,410
His wife helped put him through
architecture school.

978
01:08:33,623 --> 01:08:35,887
You found all this out on one date?

979
01:08:36,092 --> 01:08:39,357
l think he was dying to open up.
lt`s so sad.

980
01:08:39,562 --> 01:08:42,531
Now, what should l wear
to my audition?

981
01:08:42,732 --> 01:08:45,462
l`ve got an audition
for a Broadway musical.

982
01:08:45,668 --> 01:08:46,794
l`ll never get it.

983
01:08:47,003 --> 01:08:49,801
-Singing?
-Can you believe it?

984
01:08:50,206 --> 01:08:53,573
l mean, why not?
What have l got to lose?

985
01:08:53,776 --> 01:08:55,107
No, l just--

986
01:08:55,311 --> 01:08:58,405
No, l didn`t know you sang.

987
01:08:58,848 --> 01:09:02,011
You think everybody in musicals
sings well?

988
01:09:02,218 --> 01:09:05,244
No, it`s just that they sing.

989
01:09:05,455 --> 01:09:07,480
Well, you know.

990
01:09:08,791 --> 01:09:11,282
l sing a little. l mean, you know.

991
01:09:11,494 --> 01:09:13,519
l know. No, l know.

992
01:09:14,163 --> 01:09:16,188
Don`t say it that way.

993
01:09:16,399 --> 01:09:19,960
-Confidence isn`t my strong point.
-l didn`t mean that.

994
01:09:20,169 --> 01:09:23,935
l think l can fake my way
through a song. Easily.

995
01:09:26,309 --> 01:09:29,836
-Why? You don`t think it`s realistic?
-No, l didn`t-- No.

996
01:09:30,046 --> 01:09:34,449
No, l just hate to see you
put yourself in a position...

997
01:09:34,650 --> 01:09:35,912
...where you get hurt.

998
01:09:36,118 --> 01:09:38,348
You take every single rejection...

999
01:09:38,554 --> 01:09:42,081
...as confirmation
that you have no talent.

1000
01:09:42,291 --> 01:09:44,816
-Well, maybe l`ll get it.
-l hope.

1001
01:09:45,027 --> 01:09:46,460
Boy...

1002
01:09:46,662 --> 01:09:49,130
-...you know how to cut me down.
-What?

1003
01:09:49,332 --> 01:09:51,266
Can`t l say anything?

1004
01:09:51,467 --> 01:09:54,834
l sing. For chrissake,
you heard me sing!

1005
01:09:55,037 --> 01:09:56,402
Okay, l--

1006
01:09:56,606 --> 01:09:59,905
What happened?
We were having a nice time...

1007
01:10:00,109 --> 01:10:03,237
...and suddenly everything
went to bad feeling.

1008
01:10:03,446 --> 01:10:05,971
Nobody but you can do that to me.

1009
01:10:06,182 --> 01:10:09,310
Look, everything`s going your way.

1010
01:10:10,253 --> 01:10:11,686
You`re right.

1011
01:10:11,988 --> 01:10:13,580
l`m happy.

1012
01:10:14,590 --> 01:10:18,390
Why must l let my insecurities
spoil everything?

1013
01:11:02,238 --> 01:11:04,138
-Thank you very much.
-Thanks.

1014
01:11:04,340 --> 01:11:06,331
-Very nice.
-Terrific.

1015
01:11:07,009 --> 01:11:08,704
April Knox.

1016
01:11:39,075 --> 01:11:41,771
You sounded great.
You may be surprised.

1017
01:11:41,978 --> 01:11:45,243
l`m just glad we have
a catering job this week.

1018
01:11:45,448 --> 01:11:49,316
We have Mr. Levine`s 80th
birthday on Riverside Drive.

1019
01:11:49,518 --> 01:11:52,487
Or the chapel,
depending on his health.

1020
01:11:52,688 --> 01:11:55,179
Listen. David called me up.

1021
01:11:55,391 --> 01:11:58,417
-What?
-David called me last night.

1022
01:11:58,628 --> 01:12:00,994
He wants to take me
to the opera.

1023
01:12:01,197 --> 01:12:02,789
l didn`t know what to say.

1024
01:12:02,999 --> 01:12:04,023
You`re joking.

1025
01:12:04,233 --> 01:12:06,428
No, he called late last night.

1026
01:12:08,871 --> 01:12:10,498
l`m very surprised.

1027
01:12:10,706 --> 01:12:13,300
He wants to take me
to see Rigoletto.

1028
01:12:13,509 --> 01:12:15,374
And you`re going.

1029
01:12:15,578 --> 01:12:18,911
l didn`t know what to say.
At first l said no.

1030
01:12:19,215 --> 01:12:23,652
He said he`d taken you once,
and he really wanted to invite me.

1031
01:12:25,021 --> 01:12:28,286
-But l`m seeing him.
-l know. l said that...

1032
01:12:28,491 --> 01:12:31,892
...but he said he really
wanted to do it.

1033
01:12:35,498 --> 01:12:37,363
l don`t know what to say.

1034
01:12:37,633 --> 01:12:42,570
lt`s just an evening at the opera.
Did l do wrong in accepting?

1035
01:12:49,612 --> 01:12:53,514
Why would you like to
convert to Catholicism?

1036
01:12:53,716 --> 01:12:58,244
l have to believe in something
or else life is just meaningless.

1037
01:12:58,454 --> 01:13:00,752
But why did you make
the decision...

1038
01:13:00,956 --> 01:13:03,254
...to choose the Catholic faith?

1039
01:13:03,793 --> 01:13:07,456
First of all, because it`s
a very beautiful religion.

1040
01:13:07,663 --> 01:13:09,893
lt`s strong and well-structured.

1041
01:13:10,099 --> 01:13:14,399
l`m talking about the against
school prayer, pro-abortion wing.

1042
01:13:14,603 --> 01:13:16,730
So you don`t believe in God?

1043
01:13:16,939 --> 01:13:18,770
No, and l want to.

1044
01:13:18,974 --> 01:13:21,966
l`ll do anything.
l`ll dye Easter eggs.

1045
01:13:22,178 --> 01:13:25,341
l need some evidence.
l gotta have proof.

1046
01:13:25,548 --> 01:13:28,517
lf l can`t believe,
life isn`t worth living.

1047
01:13:28,718 --> 01:13:30,515
lt`s a very big leap.

1048
01:13:30,720 --> 01:13:32,847
Yes, well, can you help me?

1049
01:13:35,624 --> 01:13:38,593
l don`t understand.
l thought you`d be happy.

1050
01:13:38,794 --> 01:13:40,284
How can we be happy?

1051
01:13:40,496 --> 01:13:43,590
Because l`m giving God
serious thought.

1052
01:13:43,799 --> 01:13:49,135
-Catholicism? Why not your own people?
-l got off on the wrong foot there.

1053
01:13:49,338 --> 01:13:51,033
l need a dramatic change.

1054
01:13:51,240 --> 01:13:55,040
-You`ll believe in Jesus Christ?
-l`m gonna try.

1055
01:13:55,244 --> 01:13:58,645
-We raised you as a Jew.
-l was born that way--

1056
01:13:58,848 --> 01:14:01,874
-l`m older now.
-But why Jesus Christ?

1057
01:14:02,084 --> 01:14:04,109
Why not become a Buddhist?

1058
01:14:04,320 --> 01:14:06,220
That`s totally alien to me.

1059
01:14:06,422 --> 01:14:08,652
Aren`t you afraid of dying?

1060
01:14:08,858 --> 01:14:10,155
Why be afraid?

1061
01:14:10,359 --> 01:14:11,917
-You won`t exist.
-So?

1062
01:14:12,128 --> 01:14:16,531
-That doesn`t terrify you?
-l`m alive. When l`m dead, l`m dead.

1063
01:14:16,732 --> 01:14:18,359
Aren`t you frightened?

1064
01:14:18,567 --> 01:14:21,764
-l`ll be unconscious.
-But never to exist again?

1065
01:14:21,971 --> 01:14:24,804
-How do you know?
-lt doesn`t look promising.

1066
01:14:25,007 --> 01:14:26,497
Who knows what`ll be?

1067
01:14:26,709 --> 01:14:29,269
l`ll either be unconscious,
or l won`t.

1068
01:14:29,478 --> 01:14:32,743
lf not, l`ll deal with it then.
l won`t worry now.

1069
01:14:32,948 --> 01:14:34,074
Mom, come out.

1070
01:14:34,283 --> 01:14:38,481
Of course there`s a God, you idiot.
You don`t believe in God?

1071
01:14:38,687 --> 01:14:41,622
Then why is there so much evil
in the world?

1072
01:14:41,824 --> 01:14:44,486
On a simple level,
why were there Nazis?

1073
01:14:44,693 --> 01:14:45,853
Tell him, Max.

1074
01:14:46,061 --> 01:14:50,430
How the hell do l know?
l don`t know how the can opener works.

1075
01:16:14,717 --> 01:16:19,177
-Hi. Where`s Holly?
-She`s auditioning for a commercial.

1076
01:16:19,388 --> 01:16:23,722
-How`s she doing?
-You know Holly when she`s depressed.

1077
01:16:23,926 --> 01:16:26,258
lt`s good that we
invited her to lunch.

1078
01:16:26,462 --> 01:16:28,157
Tell her it was your idea.

1079
01:16:28,364 --> 01:16:31,458
When l try to help,
she gets defensive.

1080
01:16:31,667 --> 01:16:34,693
She`s just embarrassed
in front of you.

1081
01:16:34,904 --> 01:16:36,735
-So how are you?
-l`m okay.

1082
01:16:36,939 --> 01:16:38,531
Do you miss Frederick?

1083
01:16:38,741 --> 01:16:41,608
Elliot and l must know
someone for you.

1084
01:16:41,810 --> 01:16:45,541
How are you?
How`s Frederick--? l mean Elliot?

1085
01:16:45,748 --> 01:16:47,807
He`s fine. l guess he`s fine.

1086
01:16:48,017 --> 01:16:52,920
He`s been moody the last few months.
l don`t know what it is.

1087
01:16:53,122 --> 01:16:54,419
He`s kind of distant.

1088
01:16:54,623 --> 01:16:57,319
l try talking--
He says everything`s fine.

1089
01:16:57,526 --> 01:17:00,290
Automatically, l think the worst.

1090
01:17:00,496 --> 01:17:03,954
-He`s seeing someone else.
-No, everyone thinks that.

1091
01:17:04,166 --> 01:17:08,899
l just came from an audition which
l did not get. So what`s new?

1092
01:17:09,104 --> 01:17:13,063
They said l was too offbeat-looking,
whatever that means.

1093
01:17:13,409 --> 01:17:16,139
-But guess who`s auditioning?
-April?

1094
01:17:16,345 --> 01:17:20,907
l was very polite. l maintained
my poise. l said hello.

1095
01:17:21,116 --> 01:17:24,176
l never trusted her.
Eyes in the back of her head.

1096
01:17:24,386 --> 01:17:29,517
She and an architect are now a
definite item, which l can`t believe.

1097
01:17:29,725 --> 01:17:32,990
Though it`s put an end
to the catering company.

1098
01:17:33,195 --> 01:17:38,132
Which is why l have to speak to you.
l have to borrow more money.

1099
01:17:38,334 --> 01:17:41,735
-That`s fine.
-l decided to do some writing.

1100
01:17:41,937 --> 01:17:43,598
l`ve had it with acting.

1101
01:17:43,806 --> 01:17:48,140
These meaningless auditions.
l can`t handle another rejection.

1102
01:17:48,344 --> 01:17:52,804
Let`s face it. l have to
latch on to something in my life...

1103
01:17:53,015 --> 01:17:56,507
...something with a future.
l`m not 1 6 anymore.

1104
01:17:56,752 --> 01:17:58,276
lt`s just crazy...

1105
01:17:58,487 --> 01:18:03,356
...but l`ve got an idea for a story,
more than one...

1106
01:18:03,559 --> 01:18:07,154
...and l just need a few months
or a year even.

1107
01:18:07,363 --> 01:18:10,924
l learned about dramatic
structure from acting class.

1108
01:18:11,133 --> 01:18:16,332
That`s good. lt just seems to me
that six months or a year...

1109
01:18:16,538 --> 01:18:20,304
-...if you spend it more productively--
-Like what?

1110
01:18:20,509 --> 01:18:22,306
Well, l don`t know.

1111
01:18:22,511 --> 01:18:26,675
Didn`t mom mention something
at the Museum of Broadcasting?

1112
01:18:26,882 --> 01:18:31,410
-That`s clerical.
-Didn`t she say it`s in publicity?

1113
01:18:31,620 --> 01:18:34,817
-lt can lead to other things.
-You`re discouraging.

1114
01:18:35,024 --> 01:18:37,151
No, l`m trying to be helpful.

1115
01:18:37,359 --> 01:18:39,122
A person doesn`t say:

1116
01:18:39,328 --> 01:18:42,297
``l`m done as an actress.
Now l`m a writer.``

1117
01:18:42,498 --> 01:18:45,092
-Not at my age.
-Please. Let`s have lunch.

1118
01:18:45,300 --> 01:18:48,133
Right. Forget it.

1119
01:18:48,904 --> 01:18:52,431
l just want a salad.
You really think l`m a loser.

1120
01:18:52,641 --> 01:18:54,939
-You`re being ridiculous.
-You are.

1121
01:18:55,144 --> 01:18:57,374
-You treat me like a loser.
-How?

1122
01:18:57,579 --> 01:19:00,707
You have no faith.
You undercut my enthusiasm.

1123
01:19:00,916 --> 01:19:03,612
Not so. l`ve been very supportive.

1124
01:19:03,819 --> 01:19:08,620
l give you honest, constructive
advice. l help you financially.

1125
01:19:08,824 --> 01:19:12,419
l introduce you
to interesting, single men.

1126
01:19:12,628 --> 01:19:15,062
-All losers.
-You`re too demanding.

1127
01:19:15,264 --> 01:19:18,631
Who you fix me up with
says what you think of me.

1128
01:19:18,834 --> 01:19:21,064
-That`s not true.
-l`m mediocre.

1129
01:19:21,270 --> 01:19:24,569
Stop attacking Hannah.
She`s going through a lot.

1130
01:19:24,773 --> 01:19:28,265
-Why are you so upset?
-You keep picking on her.

1131
01:19:28,477 --> 01:19:30,707
Leave her alone. l`m suffocating.

1132
01:19:30,913 --> 01:19:34,007
Why are you so sensitive
all of a sudden?

1133
01:19:34,216 --> 01:19:36,377
Look, you wanna write, write.

1134
01:19:36,585 --> 01:19:38,780
Let`s just drop it.

1135
01:19:38,987 --> 01:19:42,514
Take a year. Take six months,
whatever you want.

1136
01:19:42,724 --> 01:19:46,353
Who knows? Maybe you`ll be
sitting with a good play.

1137
01:19:46,728 --> 01:19:50,289
What`s the matter?
You look pale. Are you okay?

1138
01:19:50,499 --> 01:19:54,765
Yeah. You know, l just got
dizzy all of a sudden.

1139
01:19:54,970 --> 01:19:57,370
l think we need to eat.

1140
01:20:13,622 --> 01:20:16,022
l can`t seem to take action.

1141
01:20:16,225 --> 01:20:19,422
l`m like Hamlet
unable to kill his uncle.

1142
01:20:19,628 --> 01:20:23,394
l want Lee, but l can`t harm Hannah.

1143
01:20:23,599 --> 01:20:26,932
And in no other area
am l a procrastinator.

1144
01:20:28,837 --> 01:20:31,067
Meanwhile, Lee has no direction.

1145
01:20:31,273 --> 01:20:34,800
She`s taking courses
at Columbia, but just randomly.

1146
01:20:35,010 --> 01:20:40,312
I try not to call her, but then
she calls me, and then I call...

1147
01:20:40,516 --> 01:20:44,384
...and we try to resist meeting,
but sometimes we meet.

1148
01:20:44,586 --> 01:20:48,147
Sometimes we argue because
I can`t split my marriage.

1149
01:20:48,357 --> 01:20:53,192
Sometimes we wind up making love,
and we both feel terrible.

1150
01:20:53,395 --> 01:20:55,454
But it`s my fault.

1151
01:20:56,999 --> 01:21:01,299
For all my education, accomplishments,
and so-called wisdom...

1152
01:21:01,503 --> 01:21:04,301
...l can`t fathom my own heart.

1153
01:21:09,411 --> 01:21:11,709
You`d like to become a Hare Krishna?

1154
01:21:11,914 --> 01:21:13,973
l`m not saying l wanna join...

1155
01:21:14,183 --> 01:21:17,584
...but you believe in reincarnation
so l`m interested.

1156
01:21:17,786 --> 01:21:19,219
What`s your religion?

1157
01:21:19,421 --> 01:21:23,357
l was born Jewish, but last winter
l tried Catholicism.

1158
01:21:23,559 --> 01:21:28,496
lt didn`t work for me. l studied
and tried, but for me it was:

1159
01:21:28,697 --> 01:21:30,187
``Die now, pay later.``

1160
01:21:30,399 --> 01:21:34,233
-l just couldn`t get with it.
-You`re afraid of dying?

1161
01:21:34,436 --> 01:21:37,234
Yeah, naturally. ln reincarnation...

1162
01:21:37,439 --> 01:21:40,272
...does my soul
pass to another human?

1163
01:21:40,475 --> 01:21:43,137
Or would l come back
as an aardvark?

1164
01:21:43,345 --> 01:21:47,509
Take our literature, read it over,
and think about it.

1165
01:21:47,716 --> 01:21:51,379
-Thank you very much.
-You`re welcome. Hare Krishna.

1166
01:21:54,423 --> 01:21:57,586
Who are you kidding?
You`re gonna be a Krishna?

1167
01:21:57,793 --> 01:22:01,661
You`re gonna shave your head
and dance around at airports?

1168
01:22:01,863 --> 01:22:03,956
You`d look like Jerry Lewis.

1169
01:22:04,733 --> 01:22:07,463
Oh, God, I`m so depressed.

1170
01:22:16,878 --> 01:22:19,574
The nights are really getting cooler.

1171
01:22:19,781 --> 01:22:22,147
Summer went so quickly.

1172
01:22:22,551 --> 01:22:24,485
Soon it`ll be fall.

1173
01:22:25,854 --> 01:22:28,482
My literature professor
really likes me.

1174
01:22:28,690 --> 01:22:31,352
It was fun being out with him
last night.

1175
01:22:31,660 --> 01:22:35,858
I feel like I`m betraying
Elliot, but that`s ridiculous.

1176
01:22:36,064 --> 01:22:39,591
Why shouldn`t I see Doug?
Elliot`s not free.

1177
01:22:40,736 --> 01:22:43,330
Just go one step at a time.

1178
01:22:43,805 --> 01:22:46,706
Let`s see what the next
few months bring.

1179
01:22:49,845 --> 01:22:54,509
You`ll be happy to know that
your money hasn`t gone to waste.

1180
01:22:54,716 --> 01:22:59,050
l have an actual first rough draft
of something l wrote.

1181
01:23:00,789 --> 01:23:03,849
l showed it to Lee.
She gave me some pointers.

1182
01:23:04,059 --> 01:23:08,120
l`m pretty near where you live.
Could l just drop it off?

1183
01:23:08,330 --> 01:23:10,594
And when you have time, read it...

1184
01:23:10,799 --> 01:23:12,994
...and we`ll talk over Thanksgiving.

1185
01:23:13,201 --> 01:23:16,967
Okay? All right. Wait. Listen!

1186
01:23:17,172 --> 01:23:19,902
Lee met an interesting guy
at Columbia.

1187
01:23:20,108 --> 01:23:23,544
Yeah, yeah.
Well, he sounds really nice.

1188
01:23:23,745 --> 01:23:26,543
All right. We`ll talk at Thanksgiving.

1189
01:23:26,748 --> 01:23:28,113
Bye-bye.

1190
01:23:29,785 --> 01:23:33,186
Here`s a song that Norma sang...

1191
01:23:33,388 --> 01:23:36,380
...on that trip we made
to the show in Buffalo.

1192
01:23:36,591 --> 01:23:39,219
Oh, was she beautiful that night!

1193
01:23:39,428 --> 01:23:40,417
Come on.

1194
01:23:40,629 --> 01:23:43,359
You were.
Don`t you remember that night?

1195
01:23:43,565 --> 01:23:46,193
She was so beautiful...

1196
01:23:46,401 --> 01:23:48,699
...that when men saw her walking...

1197
01:23:48,904 --> 01:23:52,067
...they`d drive their cars
up on the sidewalk.

1198
01:23:52,808 --> 01:23:53,968
That right, honey?

1199
01:23:54,176 --> 01:23:57,577
A slight exaggeration,
but only slight.

1200
01:24:24,406 --> 01:24:28,069
-You`ve been very cold to me tonight.
-No!

1201
01:24:28,310 --> 01:24:30,335
ls something wrong?

1202
01:24:30,846 --> 01:24:33,940
Not here. There are too many
people around.

1203
01:24:37,753 --> 01:24:40,950
l think Lee`s serious
about her new boyfriend.

1204
01:24:41,156 --> 01:24:43,488
He sounds really nice.

1205
01:24:43,692 --> 01:24:46,320
l`m happy for her.
l think she`s in love.

1206
01:24:46,728 --> 01:24:47,888
What`s wrong?

1207
01:24:48,096 --> 01:24:50,462
l`m upset about what you wrote.

1208
01:24:50,665 --> 01:24:51,689
My script?

1209
01:24:51,900 --> 01:24:54,391
-lt`s based on Elliot and me.
-Loosely.

1210
01:24:54,603 --> 01:24:58,334
Not loosely. Real specifically.
ls that how you see us?

1211
01:24:58,540 --> 01:25:02,032
Can l not accept gestures
and feelings from people?

1212
01:25:02,244 --> 01:25:03,871
Do l put people off?

1213
01:25:04,079 --> 01:25:06,445
-lt`s a made-up story.
-No, it`s exact.

1214
01:25:06,648 --> 01:25:09,276
The situations, the dialogue,
everything.

1215
01:25:09,484 --> 01:25:12,112
lt`s full of details
about Elliot and me...

1216
01:25:12,320 --> 01:25:15,551
...which l don`t see how
you could know about.

1217
01:25:15,757 --> 01:25:17,884
Our conversation about adoption?

1218
01:25:18,093 --> 01:25:19,424
Lee mentioned that to me.

1219
01:25:19,628 --> 01:25:24,122
Obviously, you told her.
l just blew it up into drama.

1220
01:25:24,332 --> 01:25:27,859
How would Lee know?
We don`t talk about everything.

1221
01:25:28,069 --> 01:25:29,866
l guess l hit a nerve.

1222
01:25:30,071 --> 01:25:34,565
You make it out like l have no needs.
Am l too self-sufficient?

1223
01:25:34,776 --> 01:25:37,244
That`s not what l meant.

1224
01:25:37,446 --> 01:25:41,314
Everybody relies on you for so much.
lt`s not a criticism.

1225
01:25:41,516 --> 01:25:44,781
-We`re grateful.
-Grateful, but you resent me.

1226
01:25:44,986 --> 01:25:47,580
l don`t wanna have this conversation.

1227
01:25:47,789 --> 01:25:51,953
l didn`t do anything wrong.
You said you were having problems.

1228
01:25:52,160 --> 01:25:54,720
Problems that are my business...

1229
01:25:54,930 --> 01:25:57,330
...which l don`t see how you know.

1230
01:25:57,532 --> 01:26:01,127
How does Lee know about these things?
They`re private.

1231
01:26:01,336 --> 01:26:03,497
Why don`t you share them with us?

1232
01:26:03,705 --> 01:26:07,835
-l don`t want to bother everyone.
-l`d like to be bothered.

1233
01:26:08,043 --> 01:26:11,740
l don`t see how you could know
unless Elliot told you.

1234
01:26:11,947 --> 01:26:13,642
No, he hasn`t.

1235
01:26:13,849 --> 01:26:16,215
lf l offended you, l`m sorry.

1236
01:26:18,753 --> 01:26:21,722
lt`s over, Elliot.
l can`t be any clearer.

1237
01:26:21,923 --> 01:26:24,551
-l deserve this--
-l`m at fault too.

1238
01:26:24,759 --> 01:26:26,659
l have such feelings--

1239
01:26:26,862 --> 01:26:29,330
To be honest, l`ve met someone else.

1240
01:26:29,531 --> 01:26:34,059
-What do you mean?
-l said l wasn`t gonna wait forever.

1241
01:26:34,269 --> 01:26:35,998
lt hasn`t been forever.

1242
01:26:36,204 --> 01:26:39,970
lt`s been a year and you`re
still married to my sister.

1243
01:26:40,175 --> 01:26:43,440
And l`m sure you`re more
in love than you know.

1244
01:26:43,645 --> 01:26:47,479
-But we made so many plans.
-ln a way, you led me on.

1245
01:26:47,682 --> 01:26:50,446
l believed you were
unhappy with Hannah.

1246
01:26:50,652 --> 01:26:53,177
l would never have
let myself be drawn in.

1247
01:26:53,388 --> 01:26:56,915
l was weak. So were you.
Now l`ve met someone else.

1248
01:26:59,561 --> 01:27:00,721
Dinner soon?

1249
01:27:00,929 --> 01:27:03,557
-About 1 5 minutes.
-Good.

1250
01:27:04,733 --> 01:27:08,191
-You`re in love overnight?
-l care a lot about him.

1251
01:27:08,403 --> 01:27:11,167
lt`s over, Elliot.
l mean it. lt`s over.

1252
01:27:15,176 --> 01:27:18,907
Sweetheart, l loved your script.
lt was so clever.

1253
01:27:19,114 --> 01:27:21,947
You`re my mother.
Not everybody`s a sucker.

1254
01:27:22,150 --> 01:27:25,085
l really liked the character
of the mother.

1255
01:27:25,287 --> 01:27:28,120
A boozy old flirt
with a filthy mouth.

1256
01:27:28,323 --> 01:27:31,349
-l`m so proud.
-Oh, Mom. Thanks.

1257
01:27:31,927 --> 01:27:33,827
A toast to Thanksgiving!

1258
01:27:34,029 --> 01:27:36,589
Are we supposed
to have beer? Yeah!

1259
01:27:36,798 --> 01:27:37,787
Let me hear it!

1260
01:27:37,999 --> 01:27:39,762
How`s that, Fletcher?

1261
01:27:39,968 --> 01:27:43,062
Now to Thanksgiving.
Here`s a little toast.

1262
01:27:43,271 --> 01:27:44,203
Bottoms up!

1263
01:27:44,606 --> 01:27:48,838
Have you been talking to Holly
or Lee about our personal life?

1264
01:27:49,044 --> 01:27:50,636
Me? Of course not.

1265
01:27:50,845 --> 01:27:52,904
There`s things in Holly`s script...

1266
01:27:53,114 --> 01:27:55,912
...that could only have come from you.

1267
01:27:56,117 --> 01:27:58,779
Look, l don`t like being accused.

1268
01:27:58,987 --> 01:28:03,287
l`m not accusing. l`m asking.
Do you find me too giving?

1269
01:28:03,491 --> 01:28:05,118
Too competent?

1270
01:28:05,327 --> 01:28:08,296
Too disgustingly perfect or something?

1271
01:28:08,496 --> 01:28:11,761
What`s come between us?
How have l alienated you?

1272
01:28:11,967 --> 01:28:15,459
-My head is throbbing.
-You never want to talk about it.

1273
01:28:15,670 --> 01:28:19,197
When l bring it up,
you change the subject.

1274
01:28:19,407 --> 01:28:22,376
We communicate less.
You sleep with me less.

1275
01:28:22,577 --> 01:28:25,478
Hannah, l am very mixed-up!
Please!

1276
01:28:25,680 --> 01:28:29,116
Do you talk to Holly or Lee
behind my back?

1277
01:28:29,317 --> 01:28:31,308
They seem to know so much.

1278
01:28:31,519 --> 01:28:34,454
Maybe l`ve asked advice
or made a joke.

1279
01:28:34,656 --> 01:28:38,387
Do you talk to Holly? Lee?
Or what? Do you phone them?

1280
01:28:38,593 --> 01:28:40,493
Leave me alone, can you?

1281
01:28:40,695 --> 01:28:43,755
Jesus, l told you.
l need someone l can matter to.

1282
01:28:43,965 --> 01:28:46,263
You matter to me. Completely.

1283
01:28:46,468 --> 01:28:50,564
l can`t be around someone who
gives so much yet needs so little.

1284
01:28:50,772 --> 01:28:52,296
l have enormous needs.

1285
01:28:52,507 --> 01:28:55,670
l can`t see them,
neither can Lee or Holly.

1286
01:29:56,604 --> 01:29:59,368
So pitch-black tonight.

1287
01:30:01,309 --> 01:30:03,368
l feel lost.

1288
01:30:04,746 --> 01:30:06,270
You`re not lost.

1289
01:30:16,424 --> 01:30:18,324
l love you so much.

1290
01:31:08,476 --> 01:31:10,034
You may not remember...

1291
01:31:10,245 --> 01:31:12,941
...but we shared the worst
night of my life.

1292
01:31:13,148 --> 01:31:14,581
l remember you.

1293
01:31:14,783 --> 01:31:17,115
You recall? l saw you in here.

1294
01:31:17,318 --> 01:31:20,754
-l thought we could replay--
-We didn`t hit it off.

1295
01:31:20,955 --> 01:31:23,651
We did everything but
exchange gunshots.

1296
01:31:23,858 --> 01:31:26,793
-How are you?
-Good. You look wonderful.

1297
01:31:26,995 --> 01:31:29,589
You do. lt was a terrible evening.

1298
01:31:29,798 --> 01:31:32,665
Remember slamming
the cab door in my face?

1299
01:31:32,867 --> 01:31:37,770
You came very dangerously close
to emasculating my nose.

1300
01:31:37,972 --> 01:31:40,770
That was a long time ago.
People change.

1301
01:31:40,975 --> 01:31:43,375
-l hope you`ve changed.
-You too.

1302
01:31:43,578 --> 01:31:46,638
Your personality left something
to be desired--

1303
01:31:46,848 --> 01:31:48,839
Namely a personality.

1304
01:31:49,284 --> 01:31:51,548
How are you? What are you doing?

1305
01:31:51,753 --> 01:31:55,587
Nothing much. A little of this,
a little of that.

1306
01:31:55,790 --> 01:31:59,385
Was that an embarrassing question?
You`re out of work?

1307
01:31:59,594 --> 01:32:02,188
-l`ve been trying to write.
-Have you?

1308
01:32:02,397 --> 01:32:04,490
-Yeah.
-What kind of stuff?

1309
01:32:04,699 --> 01:32:08,601
-You`re not interested in this.
-You can tell me. l am.

1310
01:32:08,803 --> 01:32:11,636
You must always hear,
``l wrote something.``

1311
01:32:11,840 --> 01:32:13,808
-Nobody ever said it.
-Really?

1312
01:32:14,008 --> 01:32:17,273
Would you be willing
to read something l wrote?

1313
01:32:17,478 --> 01:32:21,574
lf it would mean anything to you.
l don`t know why it would.

1314
01:32:21,783 --> 01:32:25,514
-You`ve always hated my taste.
-No, l haven`t.

1315
01:32:25,720 --> 01:32:28,917
l think it might be
a great television script...

1316
01:32:29,123 --> 01:32:31,284
...and since you`re so active--

1317
01:32:31,492 --> 01:32:33,983
l haven`t been
in television for a year.

1318
01:32:34,195 --> 01:32:35,787
You`re kidding me.

1319
01:32:35,997 --> 01:32:38,488
l may have to get back into it.

1320
01:32:38,700 --> 01:32:41,100
l`m running out of dollars.

1321
01:32:41,302 --> 01:32:45,261
But l dropped out for a year,
which is a long, dull story.

1322
01:32:45,473 --> 01:32:46,337
You okay?

1323
01:32:46,541 --> 01:32:47,974
l`m fine.

1324
01:32:48,176 --> 01:32:49,404
-How are you?
-Fine.

1325
01:32:49,611 --> 01:32:50,839
So, your script?

1326
01:32:51,045 --> 01:32:54,208
lf you`d read it,
l`d value your opinion.

1327
01:32:54,415 --> 01:32:58,181
But remember while you`re reading
and cursing my name...

1328
01:32:58,386 --> 01:33:01,321
...it`s my first script.
Well, not really.

1329
01:33:01,522 --> 01:33:04,389
My first was about
Hannah and her husband.

1330
01:33:04,592 --> 01:33:07,425
But Hannah read it
and got really angry.

1331
01:33:07,629 --> 01:33:09,688
Can`t imagine what you wrote.

1332
01:33:09,898 --> 01:33:12,958
lt wasn`t anything bad.
She-- l don`t know.

1333
01:33:13,167 --> 01:33:16,159
So l threw it out,
but l have this other one.

1334
01:33:16,371 --> 01:33:19,602
lf you want me to, l`ll read it.

1335
01:33:19,807 --> 01:33:22,708
Could l come over and read it to you?

1336
01:33:22,911 --> 01:33:26,711
Come over and read it to me?
You must be joking.

1337
01:33:26,915 --> 01:33:29,941
l`ve done my own reading
since l was 40.

1338
01:33:30,151 --> 01:33:33,143
l think it`s lucky
l ran into you. Maybe.

1339
01:33:33,354 --> 01:33:34,912
What about me?

1340
01:33:35,123 --> 01:33:38,388
l have this sensation
that l should have...

1341
01:33:38,593 --> 01:33:41,790
...kept walking and not begun
this conversation.

1342
01:33:43,064 --> 01:33:45,692
``We all play with the hand
we`re dealt.``

1343
01:33:45,900 --> 01:33:49,063
``Craig: And what hand were you dealt?``

1344
01:33:49,270 --> 01:33:51,738
``Emily: l`m two high pair.

1345
01:33:51,940 --> 01:33:53,805
Maybe even aces up.

1346
01:33:54,008 --> 01:33:57,136
The problem is,
you`ve got three deuces.``

1347
01:33:58,479 --> 01:33:59,946
That`s the end.

1348
01:34:01,416 --> 01:34:04,214
No, you can tell me straight.
lt`s okay.

1349
01:34:04,419 --> 01:34:06,546
Just tell me what you think.

1350
01:34:06,754 --> 01:34:08,312
lt`s great.

1351
01:34:08,523 --> 01:34:09,956
l-- l`m--

1352
01:34:10,158 --> 01:34:12,922
l`m speechless. l was--

1353
01:34:13,127 --> 01:34:16,961
l was not in the mood
to listen to this thing now.

1354
01:34:17,165 --> 01:34:20,794
l don`t know what to say.
l`m moved. l laughed.

1355
01:34:21,002 --> 01:34:24,438
l was on the edge of my seat.
l think it`s wonderful.

1356
01:34:24,639 --> 01:34:26,106
l`m totally stunned.

1357
01:34:26,307 --> 01:34:29,367
This is not an insult.
l`m amazed you can--

1358
01:34:29,577 --> 01:34:31,670
l just thought it was great.

1359
01:34:31,879 --> 01:34:33,904
-Really?
-Yes, l was--

1360
01:34:34,115 --> 01:34:37,107
What made you think
of that climax scene...

1361
01:34:37,318 --> 01:34:41,152
...where the architect is with
his actress girlfriend...

1362
01:34:41,356 --> 01:34:44,917
...and the schizophrenic ex-wife
stabs him to death?

1363
01:34:45,126 --> 01:34:48,892
-lt just came to me one day.
-Well, it was fabulous.

1364
01:34:49,097 --> 01:34:50,928
You really think l can write?

1365
01:34:51,132 --> 01:34:54,431
There`s maybe one or two things
l`d do differently...

1366
01:34:54,635 --> 01:34:55,932
...but who cares?

1367
01:34:56,137 --> 01:34:58,435
lt was fabulous.

1368
01:34:58,639 --> 01:35:00,766
l mean it. l`m so impressed.

1369
01:35:00,975 --> 01:35:02,966
l am. You made my day.

1370
01:35:03,478 --> 01:35:04,467
lt was great.

1371
01:35:04,679 --> 01:35:06,977
l was set to be bored stiff.

1372
01:35:07,181 --> 01:35:09,308
Would you like to have lunch?

1373
01:35:09,517 --> 01:35:12,008
l`d love to talk about that script.

1374
01:35:12,220 --> 01:35:14,381
We could do something with it.

1375
01:35:14,589 --> 01:35:18,616
And l`d like to hear what made
you suddenly drop out of life.

1376
01:35:18,826 --> 01:35:21,192
-Who cares?
-No. l care.

1377
01:35:21,396 --> 01:35:23,990
You used to be so ambitious, and....

1378
01:35:24,198 --> 01:35:26,666
God, you really liked it?

1379
01:35:48,823 --> 01:35:51,656
Gosh, you really went
through a crisis.

1380
01:35:51,859 --> 01:35:53,486
How did you get over it?

1381
01:35:53,694 --> 01:35:56,959
When l ran into you,
you seemed perfectly fine.

1382
01:35:57,165 --> 01:35:58,996
You seem fine now.

1383
01:35:59,200 --> 01:36:00,497
Well, l`ll tell you.

1384
01:36:00,935 --> 01:36:03,301
One day, a month ago, l really...

1385
01:36:03,504 --> 01:36:06,803
...hit bottom. I just felt
that in a godless universe...

1386
01:36:07,008 --> 01:36:08,976
...I didn`t want to go on living.

1387
01:36:09,177 --> 01:36:12,203
I happen to own this rifle
which I loaded...

1388
01:36:12,413 --> 01:36:14,472
...and pressed to my forehead.

1389
01:36:14,682 --> 01:36:16,980
I thought, ``I`m gonna kill myself. ``

1390
01:36:17,185 --> 01:36:19,881
Then I thought,
``What if I`m wrong?

1391
01:36:20,088 --> 01:36:23,353
What if there is a God?
Nobody really knows. ``

1392
01:36:23,558 --> 01:36:26,959
Then I thought,
``No. Maybe is not good enough.

1393
01:36:27,161 --> 01:36:29,391
I want certainty or nothing. ``

1394
01:36:29,597 --> 01:36:32,691
I remember clearly,
the clock was ticking...

1395
01:36:32,900 --> 01:36:36,097
...and I was sitting there frozen...

1396
01:36:36,304 --> 01:36:38,772
...debating whether to shoot.

1397
01:36:40,741 --> 01:36:42,368
All of a sudden,
the gun went off.

1398
01:36:42,577 --> 01:36:46,274
I was so tense I inadvertently
squeezed the trigger.

1399
01:36:46,481 --> 01:36:48,278
But I was perspiring so much...

1400
01:36:48,483 --> 01:36:51,577
... the gun slid off
my forehead and missed me.

1401
01:36:51,786 --> 01:36:54,983
Suddenly, neighbors
were pounding on the door...

1402
01:36:55,189 --> 01:36:58,716
...and the whole scene
was just pandemonium.

1403
01:36:58,926 --> 01:37:00,416
I ran to the door.

1404
01:37:00,628 --> 01:37:04,462
I didn`t know what to say.
I was embarrassed and confused.

1405
01:37:04,665 --> 01:37:07,156
My mind was racing a mile a minute.

1406
01:37:07,368 --> 01:37:11,327
I just knew one thing--
I had to get out of that house.

1407
01:37:11,539 --> 01:37:15,202
I had to get out in
the fresh air and clear my head.

